</span><span class='line'>            the <span class="nt">&lt;code&gt;</span>li<span class="nt">&lt;/code&gt;</span> elements inside the <span class="nt">&lt;code&gt;</span>nav<span class="nt">&lt;/code&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>            element. Note that you can&#39;t just write a rule for all
</span><span class='line'>            li&#39;s, or the numbered list of tasks will get messed up.
</span><span class='line'>          <span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
